We went to Big Gull lake near Northbrook Ont. in Sept. I couldn'tÂ  believe how small they were. 12 or 14 inches long. A guy was telling us about the one that got away and he said you won't believe this but I bet that pikeÂ was 2 feet long.Â  I haven't been there since 2006 and the fishing was getting bad then I thought but man I couldn't believe it. The lake is as beautiful as it ever was but the fishing pressure must be relentless. Big boats every where and blast by you at full tilt 20 yards away. How far north or westÂ do you have to go these days to get into fishing like it was 30 or 40 years ago.
